'''Ōhara Sakurai''' (大原桜井) was a {{ill|royal family member|ja|皇族|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|aristocrat|ja|貴族|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|waka poet|ja|歌人|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} during the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Initially known as '''Sakurai-Ō''' (桜井王), he adopted the name '''Ōhara Sakurai''' after his {{ill|demotion to commoner status|ja|臣籍降下|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, taking the surname {{ill|Ōhara clan|ja|大原氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Ōhara no Mahito). He was a descendant of {{ill|Emperor Bidatsu|ja|敏達天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref>『{{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}』Left Capital, Imperial Lineage</ref><ref name="o">"Onishiyama Daisōzu-den" in 『{{ill|Nihon Kōsōden Yōbunshō|ja|日本高僧伝要文抄|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}』Vol. 3</ref>, and the son of {{ill|Kawachi-Ō (Asuka period)|ja|河内王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. His official Rank was {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank|ja|従四位|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Danjon no in|ja|弾正尹|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
